description: The Kumho Museum of Art was built in Kwanhoon-dong in 1989, and later moved to its current location in 1996 due to expansion. The Kumho Museum of Art now faces the stone wall of Gyeongbokgung Palace. It is a building that combines modern and classical. The museum has 3 floors underground and 4 floors above ground. Generally, the works of the new generation of Korea are exhibited, and sometimes there are some solo exhibitions and large-scale exhibitions.
